0
00:00:05.880 --> 00:00:09.239
Friends, today we are working
with the Babinski reflex.

1
00:00:09.860 --> 00:00:12.809
It is connected to how the
child senses support and

2
00:00:12.820 --> 00:00:14.089
stability through the feet.

3
00:00:14.760 --> 00:00:18.309
If this area functions
unstably, it may show up

4
00:00:18.320 --> 00:00:22.269
as insecurity in movement,
quick fatigue, or even

5
00:00:22.280 --> 00:00:23.729
avoidance of activity.

6
00:00:24.080 --> 00:00:27.138
Through the exercises in
this block, we will activate

7
00:00:27.150 --> 00:00:30.519
the feet and help the body
build more reliable support.

8
00:00:31.340 --> 00:00:34.609
Often, these exercises
seem simple, but this

9
00:00:34.620 --> 00:00:37.229
very principle lies at
the foundation of the

10
00:00:37.240 --> 00:00:38.699
entire motor system.

11
00:00:39.060 --> 00:00:40.859
Let's go through
the exercises.

12
00:00:43.040 --> 00:00:45.069
This is also a very good
exercise, and by the

13
00:00:45.080 --> 00:00:47.839
way, even adults have
difficulties with it.

14
00:00:47.940 --> 00:00:50.869
So dear parents, it will
be useful for you too.

15
00:00:50.900 --> 00:00:52.749
If it is hard to keep
your balance, there

16
00:00:52.760 --> 00:00:53.779
is a little secret.

17
00:00:54.440 --> 00:00:56.769
Try choosing a point
directly in front of

18
00:00:56.780 --> 00:00:57.639
you and look at it.

19
00:00:58.360 --> 00:01:00.689
You need to hold the
position for a few seconds

20
00:01:00.700 --> 00:01:01.919
and alternate legs.

21
00:01:02.440 --> 00:01:05.819
Repeat the exercise
ten times on each leg.

22
00:01:05.900 --> 00:01:08.448
To make it harder, try
doing this task with

23
00:01:08.460 --> 00:01:09.919
your eyes closed.

24
00:02:05.240 --> 00:02:08.079
A simple and very
useful exercise.

25
00:02:08.120 --> 00:02:10.919
The task is to walk along
a straight line, first on

26
00:02:10.930 --> 00:02:14.689
tiptoes, then on the heels,
then on the outer edges of

27
00:02:14.700 --> 00:02:16.779
the feet, and then on the
inner edges of the feet.

28
00:02:16.840 --> 00:02:19.539
Repeat this several times,
ideally for five minutes.

29
00:04:57.880 --> 00:04:59.039
At the beginning.

30
00:04:59.100 --> 00:05:02.789
In this exercise, we massage
the foot by rolling a tennis

31
00:05:02.800 --> 00:05:06.969
ball or massage ball along the
sole, first from the toes to

32
00:05:06.980 --> 00:05:10.299
the heel, and then from the
big toe to the little toe.

33
00:05:10.920 --> 00:05:13.209
At the end, press the
ball down with the

34
00:05:13.220 --> 00:05:14.339
heel and release.

35
00:05:14.900 --> 00:05:17.719
After that, press it down
with the toes and release.

36
00:05:18.080 --> 00:05:20.419
Repeat the whole
sequence five times.

37
00:06:18.530 --> 00:06:21.079
This one is very simple
but no less effective

38
00:06:21.090 --> 00:06:21.829
because of that.

39
00:06:21.950 --> 00:06:24.009
We do 10 squats on tiptoes.

40
00:06:24.730 --> 00:06:27.239
It may not be easy to keep
your balance, but that is

41
00:06:27.250 --> 00:06:29.229
exactly why we are practicing.

42
00:06:29.870 --> 00:06:32.229
Do it slowly and carefully.

43
00:06:32.290 --> 00:06:35.799
If it is hard for the child to
maintain balance, do it next

44
00:06:35.810 --> 00:06:38.999
to a wall so the child can
lean on it if necessary

45
00:06:39.010 --> 00:06:39.909
to avoid falling.

46
00:09:00.050 --> 00:09:03.609
We have completed the
final block of exercises.

47
00:09:03.650 --> 00:09:06.959
Work with the feet is often
underestimated, but it

48
00:09:06.970 --> 00:09:09.289
is precisely what gives
the body stability.

49
00:09:10.050 --> 00:09:12.699
Even a short daily practice
can noticeably affect

50
00:09:12.710 --> 00:09:15.369
the child's overall
condition, both physically

51
00:09:15.380 --> 00:09:16.809
and emotionally.

52
00:09:16.820 --> 00:09:19.439
You can return to any of the
course blocks and combine

53
00:09:19.450 --> 00:09:21.869
them in any format that
is convenient for you.

54
00:09:22.350 --> 00:09:25.679
The main thing is to try to
maintain regularity and a

55
00:09:25.690 --> 00:09:27.469
calm, supportive approach.

56
00:09:27.790 --> 00:09:30.779
It is wonderful if you
manage to do the exercises

57
00:09:30.790 --> 00:09:33.939
a little at a time every
day, but you do not need to

58
00:09:33.950 --> 00:09:36.489
reproach or blame yourself
if you miss a day.

59
00:09:36.990 --> 00:09:39.739
We all live busy lives,
and circumstances

60
00:09:39.750 --> 00:09:41.069
often change our plans.

